## Overview

The Quiz Badge System is a **full-stack, serverless quiz application** that delivers a polished Typeform-style experience — one question at a time, animated transitions, per-question timers, and a badge awarded on completion. It is built as an artifact inside a pnpm monorepo, backed by Supabase for persistence, auth, file storage, and server-side grading logic.

### Core Features

| Feature | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Typeform-style transitions | Framer Motion `AnimatePresence` slide animations |
| Per-question countdown | Custom `useTimer` hook, enforced server-side |
| No back navigation | React Router `useBlocker` + `history.pushState` override |
| One attempt per session | `sessionStorage` guard on quiz load |
| Anonymous user identity | Supabase anonymous sign-in (zero UI) |
| Server-side grading | Supabase Edge Function (`grade-attempt`) |
| Badge award | Supabase Storage public bucket + Firestore write |
| Admin panel | Password-gated route, full CRUD on questions |
| Confetti on success | `canvas-confetti` triggered on badge unlock |

---

## Live Demo

> Access the quiz at the root route `/` and the admin panel at `/admin`.

**Demo credentials**
- Admin password: set via `VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD` environment variable

