## State Machine

The quiz UI is driven by an explicit state machine inside `QuizContext`. This makes transitions predictable, debuggable, and prevents invalid states.

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> IDLE

    IDLE --> LOADING : Begin clicked
    LOADING --> READY : questions fetched
    LOADING --> ERROR : fetch failed

    READY --> QUESTION_ACTIVE : first question displayed

    QUESTION_ACTIVE --> ANSWERED : user selects option
    ANSWERED --> QUESTION_ACTIVE : Next clicked (not last)
    ANSWERED --> SUBMITTING : Next clicked (last question)

    QUESTION_ACTIVE --> TIMED_OUT : timer reaches 0
    TIMED_OUT --> QUESTION_ACTIVE : auto-advance (not last)
    TIMED_OUT --> SUBMITTING : auto-advance (last question)

    SUBMITTING --> GRADING : attempt saved to DB
    GRADING --> PASSED : Edge Function returns passed=true
    GRADING --> FAILED : Edge Function returns passed=false

    PASSED --> [*]
    FAILED --> [*]

    note right of QUESTION_ACTIVE
        Back navigation BLOCKED
        via React Router useBlocker
    end note

    note right of GRADING
        service-role key used here
        never in browser
    end note
```

### QuizContext State Shape

```typescript
interface QuizState {
  status: 'idle' | 'loading' | 'ready' | 'active' | 'submitting' | 'grading' | 'passed' | 'failed';
  questions: Question[];
  currentIndex: number;
  answers: Answer[];
  attemptId: string | null;
  userId: string | null;
  error: string | null;
}
```

